 Lexical Lifetimes (NLL)"}, {"id": 1146616045, "node_id": "MDU6TGFiZWwxMTQ2NjE2MDQ1", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/labels/NLL-polonius", "name": "NLL-polonius", "color": "f799ea", "default": false, "description": "Issues related for using Polonius in the borrow checker"}], "state": "open", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 5, "created_at": "2018-06-26T22:32:14Z", "updated_at": "2023-06-19T14:55:19Z", "closed_at": null, "author_association": "NONE", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "Hello,\r\n\r\nI have recently been pointed to [this example](https://play.rust-lang.org/?gist=289c6fe73106c3fee425f1d50062076a&version=nightly&mode=debug):\r\n```rust\r\n#![feature(nll)]\r\n\r\nfn find_best(vec: &mut Vec<i32>) -> Option<&mut i32> {\r\n    vec.get_mut(0)\r\n}\r\n\r\nfn foo(vec: &mut Vec<i32>) -> &mut i32 {\r\n    if let Some(best) = find_best(vec) {\r\n        best\r\n    } else {\r\n        &mut vec[1]\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\nfn main() {\r\n    let mut x = vec![1, 2, 3];\r\n    *foo(&mut x) = 42;\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nTo me, the code looks sane, and looks like it should compile with NLL enabled (as the borrow to `vec` ends at the end of the `if` block, and shouldn't propagate to the `else` block), yet it looks like it doesn't.\r\n\r\nHope that helps, and as always thank you for your work on `rustc`!", "closed_by": null, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/51826/reactions", "total_count": 1, "+1": 1, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/51826/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null, "state_reason": null}